\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. T. lasiocarpa} Fischer ex DC.,{\i  Reg. Veg. Syst. Nat.}{\b  2}: 563 (1821). Glabrous except for the inflorescence, glaucous, 15-40 cm. Basal leaves cuneate, the cauline cordate-amplexicaul. Pedicels curved downwards in fruit. Silicula 3-5 × 2·5-4 mm, pubescent, strongly compressed, convex beneath, concave with incurved margins above so as to be more or less hemispherical; apex with upwardly curving beak.{\i  Dry places. S.E. Russia.} Rs(E). ({\i N. & C. Asia.})
