\pard\f0\fs28    {\b 1. G. laevigata} (Bieb.) DC.,{\i  Reg. Veg. Syst. Nat.}{\b  2}: 577 (1821). Plant 5-40 cm. Leaves oblong to obovate, the basal petiolate, the cauline with acute auricles. Pedicels curved downwards in fruit. Petals 4-6 mm. Silicula 10-12 × 2-4 mm, erect, 4-angled, attenuate at the base and apex, with 1-3 segments.{\i  Semi-deserts. S.E. Russia; rarely as a casual elsewhere.} Rs(E). ({\i C. & S.W. Asia}.)
